block content
    section#research
        a.card(href="https://www.aif.adfa.edu.au/index.html")
            img(src="/assets/aif_logo.jpg", alt="")
            h3 AIF Project
            p The AIF database is drawn from a range of official sources, including personalfiles on the National Archives website, and Embarkation and Nominal Rolls on the Australian War Memorial website.
        a.card(href="")
            img(src="/assets/awm_logo.jpg", alt="")
            h3 Australian War Memorial
            p The Memorial's purpose is to commemorate the sacrifice of those Australians who have died in war. Its mission is to assist Australians to remember, interpret and understand the Australian experience of war and its enduring impact on Australian society.
